This paper is primarily focused on information-centric networks (ICNs) and their architecture, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses access control policies and security, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses caching and latency, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and performance (cs.DC, cs.SI).
